text: Patissa fulvicepsalis is a moth in the family Crambidae. It was described by George Hampson in 1919. It is found in Malawi, Nigeria and Uganda. The wingspan is 16–22 mm. The forewings and hindwings are uniform silvery white.Annals and Magazine of Natural History (9) 4 (23): 318 ==References== Category:Moths described in 1919 Category:Schoenobiinae
title: Patissa fulvicepsalis
